analysis.info:
LEISR (Likelihood Estimation of Individual Site Rates) infer relative amino-acid or nucleotide rates from a fixed nucleotide or amino-acid alignment and tree, with possibility for partitions. Relative site-specific substitution rates are
    inferred by first optimizing alignment-wide branch lengths, and then inferring a site-specific uniform tree scaler.
